<div xmlns:java="http://xml.apache.org/xslt/java" id="centre_col"><!-- begin original content --><h1>ESSUM33670 - Shares to which
schemes can apply: Insider dealing restrictions</h1>
<br>
<p>The "Model Code for Securities Transactions by Directors of
Listed Companies" set out in the listing rules issued by the
competent authority for listing in the UK under section 74(4) of
the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (c8) imposes
restrictions on the periods and circumstances in which directors
and other officers in possession of price sensitive information may
buy and sell shares in the company. Companies whose shares are
listed on the Stock Exchange are obliged to adopt rules governing
dealings by directors in listed shares in the company, which are no
less exacting than those of the Model Rules set out in the Model
Code. Paragraph 21(5) expressly provides that restrictions imposed
by provisions which are "similar in purpose and effect" to any of
the provisions in the Model Code, are not restrictions for the

purposes of paragraph 21(4).

<br>
<br> Agreements or arrangements which go well beyond the Model

Code insider-dealing requirements should not be accepted as

"similar in purpose and effect" for the purposes of paragraph

21(5).</p>
<br>
